FBIS3-36692 "drsov027_d_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 Regional Affairs Yeltsin Allows Regions To Relax Election Rules LD0802165894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1200 GMT 8 Feb 94 LD0802165894 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] In an interview to ITAR-TASS, Sergey Samoylov, deputy head of the presidential administration directorate for cooperation with territories, said that elections to bodies of representative power are under threat in many regions of Russia. Samoylov said that because of this, Boris Yeltsin has given the Central Electoral Commission permission to allow the regions to relax strict electoral rules and to hold the elections in accordance with local circumstances.
